<br>
I know that this is a VERY heated topic and I will continue to support KCoG.  I understand the threat from SS and what it can mean to us smaller guilds, and how it will disrupt the rotations that have been followed peacefully.<br>
<br>
It has been almost a month since the first post about SS.  And what I am wondering is :<br>
<br>
During that month, how many times has Shattering Steel stolen a plane or a dragon (or any other large target)?  <br>
<br>
I have been trying to keep on top of this issue and I am unclear as to how many times, it has happened or attempted to happen.<br>
<br>
I just want to be informed and as I am sure all of you want to be too.<br>
<br>
*edited* <br>
<br>
I did miss page 2 and reread it, but my questions still stands.<br>
<br>
This is getting to be a quite heated topic.  And I guess what sparks my question is : Is it really fair to punish the members of this guild for the leaderships decisions.  I mean I have no idea how this guild is ran or (and I am sad to say) I do not know what actions by SS have done.  I guess before I turn down to aide another player I want to make sure that SS totally in the wrong.  I mean I have met a very nice person that is a members of SS, and is being a member enough malice?  <br>
<br>
Now, I understand that the idea behind the boycott is to send a message to the members that they need to speak up to there leadership. And before I started seeing the members as actual people, I totally agreed.  But, Now I am wondering if this is the best course of actions and I feel that I do not have enough information to make a good decision on this issue.<br>
<br>
Now, again I want to restate that I fully support the KGC rotations, respecting those is the only way that smaller guilds and guildless players will be able to do the large targets. However, I have elected to allow my guild members to decide for themselves.<br>
<br>
I fully understand how terrible it would be to put time and effort into a raid that wasn't possible because it was stolen.  <br>
<br>
I want us all to be informed and to act appropriately.<br>
<br>
Ok thank you all for taking the time to read this, I am sorry that is so long.  I do want to add however that I am very proud to be involved with KCoG.    <p><BR><BR>Desirrae Emeraldrain<BR>
