<br>
3 times SS has willfully infringed upon KGC guilds and the rotation. The First was against an alliance called the Natural Order (which I believe has the Silent Watch and Sign of One but correct me if I'm wrong). They tried to take Fear spawns away from TNO. The next time was in Hate. They went into a plane that had been cleared earlier in the day by Miyabi and started pharming repops. There was no guild in that night (it was a Thursday night) but the OAKS alliance (an alliance of mostly French guilds) would have had it that Friday afterwards. Because of SS, OAKS respawn was completely screwed, leaving OAKS without a full plane. Then a week from this past Saturday, they charged into Fear again. That morning (American time) OAKS had cleared Fear and that evening SS burst in. The next guild in the planes was Union Eternelle, another Europeon guild who had the plane on Sunday. SS tried killing respawns, and on discovering this, Shadowed Fates, UE, Harbingers, the Silver Daggers and a few others as well (mostly SF folks) left what they were doing and went into Fear. Without ksing or insults, the combined KGC guilds killed every spawn that was up (as we could do it faster and better than SS) before SS could get to them. They left quietly and went to the plane of Growth. <br>
<br>
On multiple occasions, myself and Kellory and I'm sure others, have attempted to talk to members and officers about what they are doing. On the last night in question, I directly asked the guild leader if it bothered him that he was messing up someone else's event that had been planned for a week. He responded with &quot;I don't care, you shouldn't schedule it, don't cry like a baby to me.&quot; Their members have all been told repeatedly by folks like me and Kellory what they are doing, and what their guild leaders are using them to do. They either don't care or like Exsodus in this thread, just don't get it and don't want to try to understand. Any member who is still in SS now KNOWS exactly what he is doing. Either they don't care or they have chosen to put their trust in leaders who do not care. They have made the decision to stay, and I don't think any of SS can claim innocence now. <br>
<br>
As I've always said, it's up to each individual to decide where they stand on this issue. Forcing someone to follow the boycott does no good. Explaining the importance of the boycott does. Keep in mind that I have never advocated harrassment or ksing or training the SS members. Explaining politely why you are withholding services is the only way to show them what they are doing wrong. <br>
<br>
Haemish MacLennan<br>
Clan Chieftan<br>
